\f0\b\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 3.3 CatBoost \'97 22 Models\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs28 \cf7 \cb3 \strokec7 CatBoost's ordered target statistics (OTS) compute leak-free TE internally at each tree node \'97 no manual TE loop is needed for raw categorical columns. This redirects FE effort to numeric interactions:\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls6\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf7 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 Minimal FE / native categoricals
\f1\b0 : Pass all 16 categorical columns via\'a0
\f2 \cb8 cat_features
\f1 \cb3 , let CatBoost's OTS handle encoding \'97 equivalent to leak-free TE, for free\cb1 \
\ls6\ilvl0
\f0\b \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 Binned cross-term interactions
\f1\b0 : Pre-compute numeric pair interactions (
\f2 \cb8 a_bin \'d7 9 + b_bin
\f1 \cb3 ) because CatBoost's symmetric (oblivious) trees apply the same split at every node of a given depth and cannot chain splits to approximate interactions \'97 they must be explicit input features\cb1 \
\ls6\ilvl0
