\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs28 \cf7 \cb3 \strokec7 The core of this solution is treating the synthetic data generation process as a source of structured signal rather than noise. The two most impactful techniques were:\cb1 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa160\partightenfactor0
\ls9\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf7 \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 Snap features
\f1\b0 : Mapping synthetic floats to their nearest original IBM value to recover the true customer archetype\cb1 \
\ls9\ilvl0
\f0\b \cb3 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec7 Decimal digit extraction
\f1\b0 : Exploiting the artifacts left by the generator's rounding/sampling behavior as classification features\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0
\cf7 \cb3 These signals were consumed by an unusually diverse ensemble \'97 37 XGBoost variants, 22 LightGBM variants, 22 CatBoost variants, 2 YDF models, 2 Nvidia cuML RF and 60 neural networks spanning 25 architectures \'97 stacked via L2-penalized logistic regression for a final ensemble\'a0
\f2 \cb8 OOF AUC of 0.91985
\f1 \cb3 .\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

